The paper deals with index coding, which is a problem in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses matrix representations and constructions, which are common in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper mentions the length of codes, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
